The hourly rate of the national minimum wage is—
. . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . .
£10.85 for a worker who is aged 18 years or over (but is not yet aged 21 years);
£8.00 for a worker who is aged under 18 years;
£8.00 for a worker to whom the apprenticeship rate applies, as determined in accordance with regulation 5.
If the rate in paragraph (1)(d) applies to a worker, the national living wage rate and the rates in paragraph 1(b) and (c) of this regulation do not apply to that worker.
